  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd. \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd: \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Pak. Disaster: Declaration of National Emergency",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "937 people have died due to unprecedented heavy rains in Pakistan. As a result, the country's government has declared a state of national emergency.",
        "Pakistan has been experiencing heavy rains for the past few months. Due to this unusually heavy rain, many places look like flooded forests.",
        "Shocking information is coming out that more than 3 crore people have lost their homes. It is said that 23 districts in Pakistan have been heavily affected by this calamity. Houses, cars being washed away and cars floating in flood waters have also been reported.",
        "Meanwhile, it has been revealed that 937 people, including 343 children, have died due to the torrential rain since the monsoon started on June 14.",
        "Especially in Sindh province only 306 people have died. 234 people were killed in Balochistan, 185 and 165 in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa and Punjab respectively due to the floods. Similarly, 37 deaths were reported in Pakistan Occupied Kashmir.",
        "Apart from this, about 8 lakh cattle have died and a total of 3 thousand kilometers of roads have been affected. It is reported that 150 km of roads and 85 thousand residences have been damaged in the last 24 hours alone.",
        "Also, 166.8 mm of rain has been recorded in Pakistan this August alone. This is 241% more than last year. Due to continuous rains, it has become difficult to carry out rescue and relief work."
      ],
